            <commentid>10458</commentid>
            <who name="Alexander Steitz">alexander.steitz</who>
            <bug_when>2009-06-19 14:30:15 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>Currently one can create a GUI or inline application, a BOM library or a contribution.

To close the gap between a BOM library and an application we should introduce the type for a &quot;native&quot; or &quot;low-level&quot; application.</thetext>
          </long_desc>
          <long_desc isprivate="0">
            <commentid>10462</commentid>
            <who name="Alexander Steitz">alexander.steitz</who>
            <bug_when>2009-06-19 16:31:37 +0200</bug_when>
            <thetext>This skeleton can be a copy of the GUI skeleton with the following modifications:

1) no &quot;asset&quot; directive in the main application class
2) extend &quot;qx.application.Native&quot;
3) no theme classes -&gt; overwrite the &quot;include&quot; job of &quot;base.json&quot;
4) no special locales -&gt; use the &quot;C&quot; fallback at the moment

For 4) there is an additional Bug #2490 to remove the locales info at all if they are not needed by the application.

</thetext>
          </long_desc>
